COVID-19. This pandemic made big changes on how we live and work.

I hope going forward with the new normal, we can sustain our momentum to perform well for our people not only in business but in engaging with our community and organizations in giving back to our communities as well.

I would also like to share that I am in my 5th year of celebrating independence. We built and opened our WCC Lounge in Moresby North East. We also conducted livelihood trainings to the Women Empowerment Group in our Community Development Projects and different programs such as the School Advisor Program that I direct.

Q. Describe your involvement in your community’s projects.

TOWARDS AUTONOMOUS PAPUA NEW GUINEA

The BEP has lots of community projects such as: The School Advisor Program and Gym Operator Training. Both of these projects are made to assist communities in participating in their welfare development activities whether it is in business or sports. A great deal in assisting the flow of activities to achieve its goals makes them relevant for the sense of ownership. The School Advisor Program give free livelihood trainings to the students and teachers of schools in Papua New Guinea.

They will be assisted in establishing their small businesses and they will become the operators providing our services. In this way, they can continue getting support from the company.
